Cosatu's Parliamentary Coordinator, Matthew Parks reacts to Labour and Employment Minister Thulas Nxesi, suspending the entire UIF management under suspension. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cosatu has welcomed Labour Minister Thulas Nxesi's decision to suspend all UIF management. Nxesi announced on Wednesday that he was placing the Commissioner, CFO and COO among others, under suspension after Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu, found irregular and fraudulent payments of COVID-19 relief funds in the UIF. READ:Â Cosatu: Warnings against PPE linked corruption fell on deaf ears "Any action by the government to deal with corruption, wasteful expenditure, fraud, we would welcome it. We have had suspicions and continuous throughout this period where many workers have come to us with complaints of corruption and fraud," said Cosatu's Parliamentary Coordinator, Matthew Parks. The trade union says more still needs to be done.